1 of the gross assessed value of the property that is the basis for the
2 determination of property taxes, subject to subsection (g).
3 (2) A taxpayer's property tax liability on other residential property
4 may not exceed two percent (2%) of the gross assessed value of
5 the property that is the basis for the determination of property
6 taxes.
7 (3) A taxpayer's property tax liability on agricultural land may not
8 exceed two percent (2%) of the gross assessed value of the land
9 that is the basis for the determination of property taxes.
10 (4) A taxpayer's property tax liability on other real property may
11 not exceed three percent (3%) of the gross assessed value of the
12 property that is the basis for the determination of property taxes.
13 (5) A taxpayer's property tax liability on personal property (other
14 than personal property that is tangible property described in
15 subsection (c)(4) or personal property that is other residential
16 property) within a particular taxing district may not exceed three
17 percent (3%) of the gross assessed value of the taxpayer's
18 personal property that is the basis for the determination of
19 property taxes within the taxing district.
20 (g) The General Assembly may, by law, authorize a unit of local
21 government to reduce the property tax liability percentage limit
22 described in subsection (f)(1) that is applied to the unit of local
23 government's property tax levy within the taxing jurisdiction of the
24 unit of local government.
25 (g) (h) This subsection applies to property taxes first due and
26 payable in 2012 and thereafter. Property taxes imposed after being
27 approved by the voters in a referendum shall not be considered for
28 purposes of calculating the limits to property tax liability under
29 subsection (f). this section.
30 (h) As used in this subsection, "eligible county" means only a
31 county for which the General Assembly determines in 2008 that limits
32 to property tax liability as described in subsection (f) are expected to
33 reduce in 2010 the aggregate property tax revenue that would otherwise
34 be collected by all units of local government and school corporations
35 in the county by at least twenty percent (20%). The General Assembly
36 may, by law, provide that property taxes imposed in an eligible county
37 to pay debt service or make lease payments for bonds or leases issued
38 or entered into before July 1, 2008, shall not be considered for purposes
39 of calculating the limits to property tax liability under subsection (f).
40 Such a law may not apply after December 31, 2019.
